                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>Monumental <objectType>base</objectType> covered with white <material>marble</material>. The base has a double grade <foreign rend="italic">crepis</foreign> below; on top, on 
                                        all four sides, a projecting moulding surmounted by 
                                         (a) two blocks from a rectangular pedestal bearing the plinths of at least four statues
                                         (block ii <dimensions><width>2.08</width> <height>0.30</height> <depth>0.31</depth> </dimensions>; 
                                        block iii <dimensions><width>1.03</width> <height>0.295</height> <depth>0.495</depth></dimensions>); 
                                        (b) under the moulding the main part of the base  (width 10.08 without <foreign rend="italic">crepis</foreign>) was cladded with 
                                        <material>marble</material> <objectType>panel</objectType>s of which several fragments are preserved, now recomposed; some fragments, 
                                        being adjacent, are pasted together, others are loose; in Roman times, the left part of (a) was re-used as <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.121.html">IRCyr2020 C.121</ref>
                                        and other statues were added on higher bases behind the former ones on the same pedestal.</p>
                                </support>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> (a) on the Southern face of the pedestal; (b) on the Southern side of the base under the moulding.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>(a) <height>0.05</height>; (b) <height precision="low">0.12</height>; very slight serifs, careful lettering, slightly slanting sigma.</handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
